<subSubSection id="C358655E861D6B3BFAFF86F5F953F54C" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861D6B3BFAFF86F5F953F54C" blockId="15.[1269,2256,2689,3189]" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">
Australian Carboniferous species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861D6B3BF84E86F5F755F532" authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[1942,2255,2689,2729]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Agnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulata" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861D6B3BF84E86F5F755F532" box="[1942,2255,2689,2729]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">Agnesia reticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20557BC861D6B3BFB2F86C4FAD2F54C" box="[1271,1352,2736,2775]" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, from Swains Gully.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358655E861D6B3BFAFF86AAF80FF3EE" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFD36D5861D6B3BFAFF86AAF80FF3EE" blockId="15.[1269,2256,2689,3189]" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">
Remarks. This is the first record of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861D6B3BF7D086AAF708F49E" authorityName="de Koninck" authorityYear="1883" box="[2056,2194,2782,2821]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Agnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861D6B3BF7D086AAF708F49E" box="[2056,2194,2782,2821]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">Agnesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="F3557645861D6B3BFB2F8778FA0EF4A8" box="[1271,1428,2828,2867]" name="Australia" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">Australia</collectingCountry>
. Agnesiaresembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861D6B3BF8C88778F849F4A8" authorityName="Holzapfel" authorityYear="1889" box="[1808,2003,2828,2867]" class="Gastropoda" family="Porcelliidae" genus="Hesperiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861D6B3BF8C88778F849F4A8" box="[1808,2003,2828,2867]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">Hesperiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a sinistrally coiled shell, with an inturned protoconch, and moderately wide umbilicus, but differs in having a reticulate ornamentation and the narrow, deep peculiar selenizone. The protoconch of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861D6B3BF8CD87B0F807F470" authorityName="de Koninck" authorityYear="1883" box="[1813,1949,3012,3051]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Agnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861D6B3BF8CD87B0F807F470" box="[1813,1949,3012,3051]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">Agnesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not yet been observed, but because of the inward coiling, as seen in 
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861D6B3BFB2D8054FA43F3DC" box="[1269,1497,3104,3143]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861D6B3BFB2D8054FA48F3DC" box="[1269,1490,3104,3143]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eotomariidae" genus="Hesperieua" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">HesperieUa</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
it is assumed that 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D56861D6B3BF87D8054F7A2F3DC" authorityName="de Koninck" authorityYear="1883" box="[1957,2104,3104,3143]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Agnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="15" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAC7861D6B3BF87D8054F7A2F3DC" box="[1957,2104,3104,3143]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="78">Agnesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a hyperstrophically coiled dextral shell.
</paragraph>
